  "text": "# Prometheus TLS Configuration Flow\n\n## Overview\n\nThe TLS configuration in Prometheus flows from the main prometheus/prometheus repository through prometheus-common (prometheus/common) to create actual tls.Config objects used in HTTP clients. This chain handles both scrape job targets and remote-write/remote-read endpoints.\n\n## Configuration Loading\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:config/config.go::LoadFile**\nThe entry point is the LoadFile function which loads and parses the YAML configuration file. This function creates a Config struct that contains the entire Prometheus configuration.\n\n## Top-Level Configuration\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:config/config.go::Config**\nThe Config struct contains arrays of scrape configurations and remote write/read configurations:\n- ScrapeConfigs: Array of ScrapeConfig for scrape job definitions\n- RemoteWriteConfigs: Array of RemoteWriteConfig for remote storage backends\n- RemoteReadConfigs: Array of RemoteReadConfig for remote querying\n\n## Configuration Structs with TLS\n\nAll three config types (ScrapeConfig, RemoteWriteConfig, RemoteReadConfig) embed HTTPClientConfig from prometheus-common, which contains the TLSConfig field:\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:config/config.go::ScrapeConfig**\nEmbeds HTTPClientConfig (inline) - supports TLS configuration via tls_config YAML field for securing connections to metric endpoints.\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:config/config.go::RemoteWriteConfig**\nEmbeds HTTPClientConfig (inline) - enables TLS configuration for remote write endpoints.\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:config/config.go::RemoteReadConfig**\nEmbeds HTTPClientConfig (inline) - enables TLS configuration for remote read queries.\n\n## Scrape Implementation Chain\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:scrape/scrape.go::newScrapePool**\nWhen a scrape job is configured, newScrapePool is called with the ScrapeConfig. This function creates a scrapePool that manages multiple scrape targets for a single job.\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:scrape/scrape.go::scrapePool**\nThe scrapePool struct stores the configuration and creates HTTP clients for scraping. It contains the client field that is created using the HTTPClientConfig from ScrapeConfig.\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:scrape/scrape.go::newScrapeClient**\nThis function takes the HTTPClientConfig from ScrapeConfig and creates an HTTP client. It calls config_util.NewClientFromConfig (from prometheus-common) to instantiate the client with proper TLS configuration.\n\n## Remote Write Implementation Chain\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:storage/remote/write.go::WriteStorage**\nManages all remote write endpoints. When initialized with RemoteWriteConfigs, it creates write clients for each configured endpoint.\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:storage/remote/client.go::ClientConfig**\nWraps the HTTPClientConfig along with other remote write-specific settings (authentication like SigV4, AzureAD, GoogleIAM, headers, etc.).\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:storage/remote/client.go::NewWriteClient**\nCreates a new WriteClient from ClientConfig. It calls config_util.NewClientFromConfig with the HTTPClientConfig field to create the underlying HTTP client with TLS support.\n\n## Remote Read Implementation Chain\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:storage/remote/storage.go::Storage**\nManages remote read operations. Uses RemoteReadConfigs to create read clients.\n\n**prometheus/prometheus:storage/remote/client.go::NewReadClient**\nCreates a new ReadClient from ClientConfig (which wraps HTTPClientConfig). Similar to NewWriteClient, it uses config_util.NewClientFromConfig to instantiate the HTTP client with TLS configuration.\n\n## Common HTTP Client Configuration\n\n**prometheus/common:config/http_config.go::HTTPClientConfig**\nThe central HTTP client configuration struct that all three configuration paths use. It contains:\n- TLSConfig field: The TLS certificate and verification configuration\n- ProxyConfig: Proxy settings\n- BasicAuth, Authorization, OAuth2: Authentication methods\n- BearerToken, BearerTokenFile: Token authentication\n- FollowRedirects, EnableHTTP2: HTTP behavior\n- HTTPHeaders: Custom headers\n\nIncludes Validate() method that ensures only one authentication method is configured and validates TLS version constraints.\n\n**prometheus/common:config/http_config.go::TLSConfig**\nThe actual TLS configuration struct with fields:\n- CA, CAFile: CA certificate for verification\n- Cert, CertFile: Client certificate\n- Key, KeyFile: Client certificate private key\n- CARef, CertRef, KeyRef: References to secret manager\n- ServerName: SNI hostname\n- InsecureSkipVerify: Disable certificate verification\n- MinVersion, MaxVersion: TLS version constraints\n\nIncludes Validate() method that ensures version constraints are valid and mutually exclusive certificate/key options.\n\n## HTTP Client Factory Functions\n\n**prometheus/common:config/http_config.go::NewClientFromConfig**\nFactory function that creates an *http.Client from HTTPClientConfig. This is the main entry point used by both scrape and remote write/read implementations. It:\n1. Validates the HTTPClientConfig\n2. Creates the RoundTripper chain using NewRoundTripperFromConfigWithContext\n3. Wraps it in an http.Client with proper redirect policy\n\n**prometheus/common:config/http_config.go::NewRoundTripperFromConfigWithContext**\nOrchestrates the HTTP transport layer, including:\n1. Creating TLS configuration via NewTLSConfigWithContext\n2. Setting up authentication (BasicAuth, OAuth2, Bearer tokens)\n3. Configuring proxy settings\n4. Adding custom headers\n5. Wrapping with metrics and tracing instrumentation\n\n**prometheus/common:config/http_config.go::NewTLSConfigWithContext**\nThe core TLS configuration builder that:\n1. Validates the TLSConfig struct\n2. Loads CA certificates (from files, inline, or secret manager)\n3. Loads client certificates and keys\n4. Creates and returns a Go crypto/tls.Config with all settings properly configured\n5. Applies TLS version constraints (MinVersion, MaxVersion)\n6. Sets InsecureSkipVerify for testing/development\n7. Sets ServerName for SNI (Server Name Indication)\n\n## Complete Configuration Flow Summary\n\n1. Prometheus loads YAML config (LoadFile)\n2. Configuration is parsed into Config struct containing ScrapeConfig, RemoteWriteConfig, RemoteReadConfig\n3. Each config embeds HTTPClientConfig which contains TLSConfig\n4. For scrape targets:\n   - newScrapePool creates scrape pools from ScrapeConfig\n   - newScrapeClient calls NewClientFromConfig with the HTTPClientConfig\n5. For remote write:\n   - NewWriteClient calls NewClientFromConfig with HTTPClientConfig from ClientConfig\n6. For remote read:\n   - NewReadClient calls NewClientFromConfig with HTTPClientConfig from ClientConfig\n7. NewClientFromConfig orchestrates the HTTP client creation:\n   - Validates HTTPClientConfig\n   - Calls NewRoundTripperFromConfigWithContext to build the transport\n8. NewRoundTripperFromConfigWithContext handles TLS setup:\n   - Calls NewTLSConfigWithContext to create *tls.Config\n   - Sets up authentication, proxy, headers, and tracing\n9. NewTLSConfigWithContext creates the final Go *tls.Config:\n   - Validates TLSConfig constraints\n   - Loads certificates from files or inline sources\n   - Applies version constraints and verification settings\n   - Returns ready-to-use tls.Config for the HTTP client\n\nThe separation between prometheus (main Prometheus server) and prometheus-common (shared library) allows other Prometheus ecosystem tools (exporters, alertmanagers, etc.) to use the same standardized HTTP client configuration and TLS handling."
}

